'''Mladen Jurkas''' (born 7 October 2007) is a Bosnian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Premier League of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian Premier League]] club [[FK Borac Banja Luka|Borac Banja Luka]] and the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

==Club career==
Jurkas started his professional career at [[FK Borac Banja Luka|Borac Banja Luka]] in 2025, at the age of 16.

==International career==
In May 2026, Jurkas was named in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]]'s squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nap.ba/post/golman-borca-mladen-jurkas-pridruzio-se-pripremama-zmajeva|title=Borac goalkeeper Mladen Jurkas joins the Dragons' preparations|date=30 May 2026|website=NAP.ba}}</ref>

